<DOC><DOCNO> AP891103-0002 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-03-89 2345EST</FILEID><FIRST>u w AM-SummitLeak     11-03 0111</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Summit Leak,100</SECOND><HEAD>President Steamed Over Leak Of Seawater Summit</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Bush wants to know who leaked wordof his pending summit meeting with Soviet President MikhailGorbachev, and White House aides have standing orders to report allcontact with journalists, The Washington Post reported in Saturdayeditions.   Bush was ``fit to be tied'' over the leaked report of thesummit, which appeared in the Post 12 hours before its scheduledsimultaneous announcement in Washington and Moscow, the newspaperreported, citing unidentified administration sources.   The president has ordered a ``full scale witch hunt,'' in thewake of the leaked report, the newspaper quoted a source as saying.</TEXT></DOC>